#  HRS Applicant Dashboard - Environment Variables Template

Copy this file to `.env.local` and update with your values

## Development Environment

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api/v1
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
VITE_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# Web3 & Blockchain Configuration
VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL=http://localhost:8545
VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0x0000000000000000000000000000000000000000

# Contract ABI (JSON string)
VITE_CONTRACT_ABI=[{"inputs":[],"name":"example","outputs":[],"stateMutability":"nonpayable","type":"function"}]

# Network Configuration
VITE_CHAIN_ID=1337
VITE_NETWORK_NAME=localhost

# Application Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME= HRS
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=true
```

## Production Environment

```env
# API Configuration (update with production URL)
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://api.v-rec.com/api
VITE_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# Web3 & Blockchain Configuration (update with production URLs)
VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL=https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/YOUR_INFURA_KEY
VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0x1234567890123456789012345678901234567890

# Contract ABI
VITE_CONTRACT_ABI=[{"inputs":[{"name":"jobId","type":"uint256"},{"name":"applicant","type":"address"}],"name":"logJobApplication","outputs":[],"stateMutability":"nonpayable","type":"function"}]

# Network Configuration
VITE_CHAIN_ID=1
VITE_NETWORK_NAME=ethereum-mainnet

# Application Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME= HRS
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=false
```

## Staging Environment

```env
# API Configuration
VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://staging-api.v-rec.com/api
VITE_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# Web3 & Blockchain Configuration (use testnet)
VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL=https://goerli.infura.io/v3/YOUR_INFURA_KEY
VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS=0x0987654321098765432109876543210987654321

# Contract ABI
VITE_CONTRACT_ABI=[...]

# Network Configuration
VITE_CHAIN_ID=5
VITE_NETWORK_NAME=ethereum-goerli

# Application Configuration
VITE_APP_NAME= HRS (Staging)
VITE_APP_VERSION=1.0.0
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=true
```

## Local Development with Hardhat

```env
# When running local Hardhat blockchain
VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:3001/api
VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8545
VITE_CHAIN_ID=31337
VITE_NETWORK_NAME=hardhat
VITE_DEBUG_MODE=true

# Get contract address from Hardhat deployment
# Get ABI from your build artifacts folder
```

## Environment Variables Reference

| Variable | Description | Example |
|----------|-------------|---------|
| `VITE_API_BASE_URL` | Backend API endpoint | `http://localhost:3001/api` |
| `VITE_API_TIMEOUT` | API request timeout (ms) | `30000` |
| `VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL` | Blockchain RPC endpoint | `http://localhost:8545` |
| `VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS` | Smart contract address | `0x1234...` |
| `VITE_CONTRACT_ABI` | Contract function ABI | `[{...}]` |
| `VITE_CHAIN_ID` | Network chain ID | `1` (mainnet), `5` (goerli) |
| `VITE_NETWORK_NAME` | Network display name | `ethereum-mainnet` |
| `VITE_APP_NAME` | Application name | ` HRS` |
| `VITE_APP_VERSION` | App version | `1.0.0` |
| `VITE_DEBUG_MODE` | Enable debug logging | `true` or `false` |

## How to Use

### Step 1: Create .env.local file

```bash
cd frontend/new
cp .env.example .env.local
```

### Step 2: Update with your values

Edit `.env.local` with:
- Your API endpoint
- Your blockchain RPC provider
- Your deployed contract address
- Your contract ABI

### Step 3: Verify in code

Your Vue/React component can access these:

```javascript
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;
const contractAddress = import.meta.env.VITE_CONTRACT_ADDRESS;
```

## Getting Contract ABI

### From Hardhat
```bash
cat artifacts/contracts/VRECApplications.sol/VRECApplications.json | jq '.abi'
```

### From Etherscan
1. Go to your contract on Etherscan
2. Click "Contract" tab
3. Copy the ABI JSON
4. Paste in VITE_CONTRACT_ABI

## Getting RPC URLs

- **Local**: `http://127.0.0.1:8545`
- **Goerli Testnet**: `https://goerli.infura.io/v3/YOUR_KEY`
- **Sepolia Testnet**: `https://sepolia.infura.io/v3/YOUR_KEY`
- **Mainnet**: `https://mainnet.infura.io/v3/YOUR_KEY`

Get free Infura API key at https://app.infura.io

## Chain IDs Reference

| Network | Chain ID |
|---------|----------|
| Hardhat | 31337 |
| Localhost | 1337 |
| Goerli | 5 |
| Sepolia | 11155111 |
| Mainnet | 1 |

## Security Notes

 **IMPORTANT**:
- Never commit `.env.local` to version control
- Never share private keys in environment variables
- Use `.env.local` for local development only
- For production, use secure environment variable management
- Rotate Infura keys regularly
- Use API rate limiting in production

## Example Smart Contract ABI

```json
[
  {
    "inputs": [
      {"name": "jobId", "type": "uint256"},
      {"name": "applicant", "type": "address"}
    ],
    "name": "logJobApplication",
    "outputs": [],
    "stateMutability": "nonpayable",
    "type": "function"
  },
  {
    "inputs": [
      {"name": "simulationId", "type": "uint256"},
      {"name": "applicant", "type": "address"}
    ],
    "name": "logSimulationStart",
    "outputs": [],
    "stateMutability": "nonpayable",
    "type": "function"
  },
  {
    "anonymous": false,
    "inputs": [
      {"indexed": true, "name": "jobId", "type": "uint256"},
      {"indexed": true, "name": "applicant", "type": "address"},
      {"indexed": false, "name": "timestamp", "type": "uint256"}
    ],
    "name": "ApplicationLogged",
    "type": "event"
  }
]
```

## Accessing Environment Variables in Code

### React/Vite

```javascript
// String values
const apiUrl = import.meta.env.VITE_API_BASE_URL;

// Parse JSON
const abi = JSON.parse(import.meta.env.VITE_CONTRACT_ABI);

// Numbers
const chainId = parseInt(import.meta.env.VITE_CHAIN_ID);

// Booleans
const isDebug = import.meta.env.VITE_DEBUG_MODE === 'true';
```

### Runtime Checks

```javascript
if (!import.meta.env.VITE_WEB3_PROVIDER_URL) {
  console.warn('Web3 provider not configured');
}
```

